Graham is a seasoned Professional Services developer working on Service Template development for 5+ years. While he is excited to work on new development, there are inherent pains which he faces on a daily basis

•Data Modeling • Resource library • Searching for resources • Versioning and branching • Code merge • Unit testing/ Integration testing • Lack of sharing or export options • Multi -tasking is another frustration• Complex DDUI • Execution time • Launching/ new installations
Pain Points
Gains

•Ease and reduction of time taken for launching, developing, implementing changes and testing • Extensibility to search • Integration of versioning and branching • Graphical view of code • Ease of debugging and analysis of data • Ease of use for semi -skilled resources•
